oai_dc:dc.dc:title: 1865 list of prices for medical treatments
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Middle Tennessee doctors' document with following prices for primarily female procedures: Prescriptions and Medicines are $1.50, Natural Labor with mileage is $10.00, Complicated or Instrumental Labor with mileage is $20, Examination per Vaginum is $2.00, fractures and dislocations is $5 to $25, tooth extracting is $1.00, and treatment of "Gonorrhoe and primary Syphilis" is $10, in advance. Several doctors are listed. Document may be military in origin and may concern regulation of Nashville prostitution.
